8 Section 15. KRS 121.110 is amended to read as follows:
9 (1) There is hereby created as an independent agency of state government a Kentucky
10 Registry of Election Finance. The registry shall be composed of seven (7) members
11 appointed as provided herein. The registry shall remain independent of any other
12 agency or department of state government. Members shall be at least twenty-five
13 (25) years of age, registered voters in Kentucky, not announced candidates for
14 public office, not officers of a political party's state central executive committee,
15 shall not have been convicted of an election offense, and shall be persons of high
16 ethical standards who have an active interest in promoting fair elections.
17 Appointees shall be subject to Senate confirmation at the next regular session of the
18 General Assembly following appointment, or at the next special session if included
19 in the Governor's call. Appointees shall have full power to serve until any vote of
20 nonconfirmation.
21 (2) Members of the registry shall be selected as follows:
