22 (1) No contribution shall be made or received, directly or indirectly, other than an
23 independent expenditure, to support inauguration activities or to support or defeat a
24 candidate, slate of candidates, constitutional amendment, or public question which
25 will appear on the ballot in an election, except through the duly appointed campaign
26 manager, or campaign treasurer of the candidate, slate of candidates, or registered
27 committee. Any person making an independent expenditure, shall report these
